  "evidence": [
    {
      "quote": "Revenue collections during FY 2002 were dramatically lower than FY 2001 collections. Corporate and individual income tax receipts especially suffered from a declining economy and capital gain losses.",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "The approved budget allows a $20 base budget per pupil increase for public education and essentially holds higher education at prior year levels.",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "To finance the restorations, the Legislature passed a revenue package, SB 39, that is projected to increase receipts in FY 2003 by $252 million.",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "The reduction was based on forecasted changes in Kansas personal income and an expected $11.0 million reduction to receipts resulting from the 2001 federal tax law changes.",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "The estimate also includes the anticipated $25.0 million reduction in tax liability that will result from the Job Creation and Worker Assistance Act of 2002.",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "These changes are expected to increase State General Fund receipts by $270.1 million.",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "Estimated Effect of the Tax Reductions Enacted during Graves' Administration (Dollars in Millions)",
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "quote": "The other bill that included financing for the FY 2003 budget was 2002 HB 3011, which increased motor fuel taxes and vehicle registration fees to finance the Comprehensive Transportation Program.",
      "note": "Page 25"
    }
